'''Green Library''' ('''Biliothèque verte''' in [[French language|French]]) is a [[Collection (publishing)|collection]] of French books for children created in 1923 by [[Hachette (publisher)|Hachette]], which is characterized by a green cover. The books had commercial success, The Green Library reached its peak between 1955 and 1980.

