{{expand language|topic=|langcode=ZH|otherarticle=乾清门|date=November 2017}}
[[File:Pictures from The Forbidden City (12034899975).jpg|thumb|right|Gate of Heavenly Purity, 2013]]
[[File:Chien-ching-mên, Thor im fünften Hof der Verbotenen Stadt 2.jpg|thumb|right|Historical image]]
The '''Gate of Heavenly Purity''' is the main gate of the Inner Court of the [[Forbidden City]], in [[Beijing]], China. The gate once led people to Forbidden City's residential quarters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=C-vbDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA65&lpg=PA65&dq#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=China - National Geographic|first=Damian|last=Harper|date=7 February 2017|publisher=National Geographic Books|accessdate=13 November 2017|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>[http://www.timeoutbeijing.com/features/Visiting_Beijing-Essential_Beijing/157004/Time-Outs-ultimate-guide-to-Beijings-Forbidden-City.html] {{dead link|date=November 2017}}</ref> It is connected to the [[Palace of Heavenly Purity]], and near the [[Gate of Thriving Imperial Clan]].

Two gilded Chinese lion sculptures are installed outside the gate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.waymarking.com/waymarks/WM6FQR_Lions_at_the_Gate_of_Heavenly_Purity_in_Forbidden_City_Beijing_China|title=Lions at the Gate of Heavenly Purity in Forbidden City|website=Waymarking.com|accessdate=12 November 2017}}</ref>

